Text.Value: Ha! You are a worm, lecturing the crow about to consume you.
Wait - no. It cannot be. Were you the one who took my poor Astarion under your wing, only to abandon him so cruelly?
When you do not return from this place, he will want to flee. He will want to leave this city and all its horrors behind. But he won't.
I am the immortal Cazador Szarr! And you will be mine.
Attack.
You think you can stand against me?
Truly? I could have sworn I knew you. Perhaps it is your plain, forgettable face.
No, you will stay here. You will be mine, now and forever!
All I need do is ensure you never return to him, and that sweet idiot will soon come searching for you.
Oh, you have been an interesting distraction for him, no doubt, but your time together is over.
And you are certain he will not come to me?
No, he is afraid. He is afraid because all he has ever known is you and me, and without us he is nothing.
Oh, he's probably bricking it.
He tried to bite me!
Nope, never met the guy.
Trust? Astarion? One of his few redeeming features is that he never trusts anybody.
I am the immortal Cazador Szarr. And I always get what I want.
Perhaps he convinces himself he can save you, perhaps he slinks back like a beaten dog. It does not matter, either way he will return. Either way he will be mine.
Seven thousand souls, each bearing the scar of the one that brought them to me, stand ready to be sacrificed.
I'm here to discuss handing him over. I can save you a lot of trouble.
I won't let you use me as bait.
Has he sent you here to parley on his behalf? Will he not even speak to his own family?
Please, did Astarion tell you nothing about me?
But as you are here, it would be a shame to waste the audience.
In my defence, he was being a dick.
But cross me and, I promise, I will deliver you an eternity of suffering.
Blessed are you to be the first I shall consume when I become the Vampire Ascendant.
You would turn on him? How delightfully treacherous. Hmm...
In their blood I shall be reborn, free to walk in the sun's rays. Free from sanguinary hunger. And free to crush any that stand against me with merciless power.
Now that he is mine once more, I have everything I need. This ritual - this Black Mass that has been centuries in the making - is finally ready.
No, you are not leaving. Not now, not ever.
Very well, I give you one chance. Return with my wayward boy, and perhaps I will let you live.
This is the Rite of Profane Ascension - attempted only once in legend.
What if I just bring Astarion to you? I could walk him right in here.
Witness the birth of the Vampire Ascendant! Ecce dominus!
He's not coming - and you can't complete this ritual without him.
That is why he will come back to me. Because he yearns to be with his people. Because this is all he knows.
I believed all our guests had been dealt with upstairs. Werewolves leave so much to be desired.
I hope we understand each other. Now, go.
You will not stop this ritual. Nothing will stop this ritual.
How... succinctly put. Indeed, he is terrified.
You're not his family - you're a monster.
He will come here, because he knows nothing else. Because he is incapable of anything else.
You presume to know the boy better than I? I who made him?
He's fine. He's safe from you.
He's worried about me and wants me to get back safe.
You came here wholly ignorant? With no concept of what you were about to witness?
Taken by mind flayers, then monster hunters, then you. That's a run of bad luck.
What is family, if not the monsters we are obliged to love?
No, your timing is perfect. All is in place.
I wish I could believe you, I truly do. But alas, I have been cursed with inordinate intelligence and am not about to give up this bird in the hand.
Cazador, I presume? What is going on here?
Tell me, then - what is he feeling? Right this moment, in whatever rathole he is cloistered?
When you don't return, he will realise he has nowhere else to go. He will come to me. And he will be mine.
In their blood I shall be reborn, free to walk in the sun's rays. Free from sanguinary hunger. And free to crush any who stand against me with merciless power.
Hardly. Even he knows better than that. Nowhere is safe.
An audience to what, exactly?
I see you chose the latter. Very well, then.
Now this is unexpected. You who follow on the heels of our poor, lost son.
This is the Rite of Profane Ascension - attempted only once in legend.
Is this a bad time?
Seven thousand souls, each bearing the scar of the one who brought them to me, stand ready to be sacrificed.
I know all about your ritual. I won't let you go through with it.
Ha! Oh, you sweet idiot. No.
A bold offer. And one I would be a fool to accept.
He trusts me to end this.
What do you want from him?
But it matters not. You are here now, just as we consummate our most profane rite.
And you call yourself his family? You're a monster.
My instructions were clear - bring me back the boy or suffer.
You came here wholly ignorant? With no concept of what you were about to witness?
Please, I care not for your petty drama. In truth, you made all of this possible.
He's not coming. You'll never see him again.

Synopsis:
Player approaches Cazador who is preparing for the Black Mass Ritual.
Cazador is suprised.
